==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hertz
<hw>Hertz</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[from the German
physicist <person>Heinrich <etsep>Hertz</etsep></person>.]</ety> <def>a
unit of frequency equal to one cycle per second; it is abbreviated
<abbr>Hz</abbr>. It is commonly used to specify the frequency of radio
waves, and also the clock frequencies in digital computers. For these
applications, kilohertz and megahertz are the most commonly used units,
derived from <ex>hertz</ex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Hertzian</ent>⟦br⟧
